      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"middle ground\" thing but it feels like a bit of an easy answer. if you really look at the data, isn't it true that massive debt eventually causes a total economic collapse, making social programs impossible anyway? so wouldn't prioritizing debt reduction just be the more logical and responsible way to go?",
